fuses to serve him which shows their ignorance for hearing disabilities. %0a%3c %0a%3c Although the languages of English and ASL are completely different, the employees could have given the man the benefit of doubt and at least serve him. Instead, they wasted their own time and resources by throwing out his order. If he was faking it, the wasted food has the same outcome in both scenarios. %0a%3c %0a%3c As a result of the video, more people should understand ASL or at least be able to communicate around it. All people should be treated with fairness, and it was wrong for employees of McDonald's to dismiss someone's disability and essentially ignore them. I think it would help if at least one person in a business understood ASL to deter future discrimination.  %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
